1.7
log
@We want to use @@unexec here and not @@unexec-delete.
The reason is that if a theme is removed after updating to a new version,
then we are left over with a useless cache file because we are using
pkg_add -u and not pkg_delete.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
# $OpenBSD: Makefile,v 1.6 2011/05/19 07:57:51 ajacoutot Exp $
d5 3
a7 3
DISTNAME=		human-icon-theme_0.33.6ubuntu2
PKGNAME=		human-icon-theme-0.33.6
REVISION=		3
d11 1
a11 1
MASTER_SITES=		http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/pool/main/h/human-icon-theme/
d19 3
a21 1
WRKDIST=	${WRKDIR}/${DISTNAME:S/_/-/}
@


